<dt><a name='accept'></a><a name="accept_NEWSOCKET,GENERICSOCKET"
>accept NEWSOCKET,GENERICSOCKET <!--
	INDEX: accept
--></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Accepts an incoming socket connect, just as accept(2) does. Returns the packed address if it succeeded, false otherwise. See the example in <a href="/~flora/perl-5.14.2/pod/perlipc.pod#Sockets:_Client/Server_Communication" class="podlinkpod"
>&#34;Sockets: Client/Server Communication&#34; in perlipc</a>.</p>

<p>On systems that support a close-on-exec flag on files, the flag will be set for the newly opened file descriptor, as determined by the value of $^F. See <a href="/~flora/perl-5.14.2/pod/perlvar.pod#$^F" class="podlinkpod"
